I’m really excited about the England squad Stuart Lancaster has selected and delighted to see Danny Cipriani and Nick Easter involved again.

This is a momentous year for English rugby with a World Cup just around the corner and I’m pleased Lancaster has been bold enough to select two of the Premiership’s form players in a squad full of high-quality Test match animals.

England may be missing a few players through injury but they have so much depth that there are no excuses for underperforming in this Six Nations. It’s time to deliver. 

