How will England choose to play? Bath proved in their fantastic win over Toulouse at the weekend that there are English-qualified players who are capable of shredding defences with their pace and skills — Jonathan Joseph was absolutely outstanding at outside centre.

I’d pick Joseph against Wales alongside his Bath team-mate Kyle Eastmond. I’d then insist on the Millennium Stadium roof being shut to ensure perfect conditions. Then I’d order my team to go out and attack.

It’s going to be fascinating to see if Lancaster can hold his nerve when it comes to whittling down his squad and I’ll be disappointed if he reverts to a conservative selection policy. 

Toulon forward Steffon Armitage was overlooked for the training squad by Lancaster

